The greatest strategy for brand-new IT start-ups to target both the Chinese and Islamic markets would be to carry out in-depth market research and customize their goods and services to fit the unique requirements and preferences of each market. Language localization and cultural sensitivity are two crucial factors to take into account. Understanding and upholding the cultural and religious values of the Muslim market is essential, and it is equally important to make sure that all materials and communications are translated and presented in a manner that Chinese customers can readily comprehend. Additionally, forming alliances and working together with nearby companies and influencers may help you engage and reach these target audiences. 